20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1914 of Title 69, unless there
23 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 12436 Page 1

1 A. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall establish
2 the Oklahoma Industrial Access Improvement Grant Program to provide
3 funding for roadway and traffic engineering and construction support
4 for industrial access projects in eligible municipalities with a
5 population of over seven hundred and fifty thousand (750,000)
6 according to the latest Federal Decennial Census. The Department
7 shall administer the Program and ensure compliance with state and
8 federal transportation regulations. The Program shall include
9 development of grants to be awarded to applicants for planning,
10 design, right-of-way acquisition, and construction of infrastructure
11 improvements that enhance industrial site accessibility which shall
12 include, but may not be limited to:
13 1. Roadway expansions and improvements;
14 2. Bridge enhancements;
15 3. Intersection modifications;
16 4. Freight corridor improvements; and
17 5. Traffic signalization upgrades.
18 B. The Department shall develop an application process,
19 including deadlines, required documentation, and evaluation
20 criteria, to determine project eligibility and priority.
21 Applications shall include, but may not be limited to:
22 1. A description of the proposed industrial access project;
23 2. A statement of need and anticipated economic impact;
24 3. Engineering and cost estimates;
Req. No. 12436 Page 2

1 4. A project timeline; and
2 5. Evidence of local matching funds, if applicable.
3 C. The Department shall allocate grants based on available
4 funds and the relative merit of applications. The Department may
5 establish matching requirements, wherein a percentage of project
6 costs shall be covered by the eligible municipality or private-
7 sector partners.
8 D. The Department is authorized to promulgate rules to
9 effectuate the provisions of this section.
10 E. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
11 fund for the Department to be designated the "Oklahoma Industrial
12 Access Improvement Grant Program Revolving Fund". The revolving
13 fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year
14 limitations, and shall consist of all monies designated for deposit
15 to said fund. All monies accruing to the credit of said revolving
16 fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the
17 Department for purposes of awarding grants by and through the
18 Department pursuant to subsection A of this section and for the
19 operating expenses of the Department.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
